\'Off-the-Record Messaging\' is a security system designed to enable privacy by mimicking the characteristics of a private conversation in the real world, including Encryption, Authentication, Deniability and Forward Secrecy.
The OTR-protocol is compatible with desktop chat clients such as Adium or Pidgin.
